<div class="container my-5">
  <div class="text-center">
  <h1 class = "h3 mb-2">Ball Allocation Task</h1>
  <button type="button" class="btn btn-link" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#instructionsModal">
    View Instructions
  </button>
    
  </div>
  <% if current_user.allocation_tests.empty? %>
        <script>
      $(document).ready(function(){
            
              $('#instructionsModal').modal('show');
            });
    </script>
  <% end %>
<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="instructionsModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="instructionsModalLabel" >
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="instructionsModalLabel">Instructions (Stage 2)</h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>
        Congratulations on passing the first stage!
        </p>
        <p>
          This next stage is to measure your confidence of your performance in Stage 1
        </p>
        <p>
          You have 100 balls which represent 100 percent of your confidence
        </p>
        <p>
          Your task is to allocate the balls to each of these bins
        </p>
        <p>
          Let the number of balls represent your percentage of confidence that you got that number of sliders correct
        </p>
        <div>
          <div>This is the ball allocation task</div>
          <%= image_tag "ball-allocation.png", class: "img-fluid" %>
          <p>
            In the example above, our participant placed 22 balls in the bin with the interval of 91-105. This means that he is 22% sure that he got somewhere between 91 to 105 sliders correctly out of all the sliders he answered in Stage 1.
          </p>

          <p><b>You don't need to fill all the bins, but all 100 balls must be allocated</b></p>

          <p>Note: The more balls you place in the bin that contains your actual number of correct sliders, the greater your chance is of winning bonus points, so guess wisely!</p>
          
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal">Start</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

  <%= render 'form', allocation_test: @allocation_test %>


</div>
